{%- comment -%} Materials Guide — Azoir {%- endcomment -%}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'pages.css' | asset_url }}" media="print" onload="this.media='all'">
<noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'pages.css' | asset_url }}"></noscript>

<section class="mg-hero">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <span class="ap-eyebrow">What we work with</span>
    <h1 class="mg-hero__title">Every material, chosen deliberately.</h1>
    <p class="mg-hero__sub">The metal and stones we recommend for your commission depend on how you'll wear it, what it means, and how long you want it to last. Here's what you need to know before you choose.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mg-metals">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <h2 class="ap-section-title">Precious metals</h2>
    <div class="mg-metal-grid">

      <div class="mg-metal">
        <div class="mg-metal__swatch mg-metal__swatch--yellow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="mg-metal__info">
          <h3 class="mg-metal__name">18k Yellow Gold</h3>
          <div class="mg-metal__attrs">
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Purity</span><span class="mg-attr__val">75% gold</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Durability</span><span class="mg-attr__val">High</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Maintenance</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Low</span></span>
          </div>
          <p class="mg-metal__desc">The most classic choice for fine jewellery. Warm, rich, and resistant to tarnish. 18k strikes the ideal balance between purity and durability — pure gold is too soft for everyday wear. Yellow gold is the most traditional choice for engagement and heirloom pieces, and it suits every skin tone.</p>
          <p class="mg-metal__best">Best for: engagement rings, heirloom pieces, everyday wear.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mg-metal">
        <div class="mg-metal__swatch mg-metal__swatch--white" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="mg-metal__info">
          <h3 class="mg-metal__name">18k White Gold</h3>
          <div class="mg-metal__attrs">
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Purity</span><span class="mg-attr__val">75% gold</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Durability</span><span class="mg-attr__val">High</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Maintenance</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Medium</span></span>
          </div>
          <p class="mg-metal__desc">White gold is yellow gold alloyed with white metals (typically palladium) and finished with a rhodium plating for its bright, reflective surface. The plating will wear over time on rings with daily friction — typically every 1–3 years — but replating is a quick, affordable service.</p>
          <p class="mg-metal__best">Best for: contemporary designs, diamond settings, minimalist aesthetics.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mg-metal">
        <div class="mg-metal__swatch mg-metal__swatch--rose" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="mg-metal__info">
          <h3 class="mg-metal__name">18k Rose Gold</h3>
          <div class="mg-metal__attrs">
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Purity</span><span class="mg-attr__val">75% gold</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Durability</span><span class="mg-attr__val">High</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Maintenance</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Low</span></span>
          </div>
          <p class="mg-metal__desc">The warmth of yellow gold with a softer, more romantic tone. Rose gold gets its colour from a copper alloy, and — unlike white gold — requires no plating. Its colour is permanent and deepens very slightly with age, which many clients love. It flatters warm skin tones particularly well.</p>
          <p class="mg-metal__best">Best for: engagement rings, anniversary pieces, stacking rings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mg-metal">
        <div class="mg-metal__swatch mg-metal__swatch--platinum" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="mg-metal__info">
          <h3 class="mg-metal__name">Platinum</h3>
          <div class="mg-metal__attrs">
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Purity</span><span class="mg-attr__val">95% platinum</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Durability</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Exceptional</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Maintenance</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Low</span></span>
          </div>
          <p class="mg-metal__desc">The premium choice for pieces that need to last generations. Platinum is denser and more durable than gold, naturally white, and hypoallergenic. It develops a satin patina over time rather than wearing away — metal is displaced, not lost. For this reason, it's the preferred material for heirloom-grade commissions and engagement rings intended to last a lifetime.</p>
          <p class="mg-metal__best">Best for: heirloom pieces, engagement rings, diamond solitaires.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mg-metal">
        <div class="mg-metal__swatch mg-metal__swatch--silver" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="mg-metal__info">
          <h3 class="mg-metal__name">Sterling Silver</h3>
          <div class="mg-metal__attrs">
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Purity</span><span class="mg-attr__val">92.5% silver</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Durability</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Medium</span></span>
            <span class="mg-attr"><span class="mg-attr__label">Maintenance</span><span class="mg-attr__val">Medium</span></span>
          </div>
          <p class="mg-metal__desc">An elegant, accessible choice for everyday pieces and bolder statement designs. Silver will tarnish over time with exposure to air and skin oils — this is natural and reversible with a polishing cloth. For pieces worn daily, we recommend regular light cleaning. Silver is lighter than gold or platinum, which makes it a natural choice for larger, more sculptural pieces.</p>
          <p class="mg-metal__best">Best for: statement pieces, pendants, everyday rings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mg-stones">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <h2 class="ap-section-title">Stones &amp; sourcing</h2>
    <p class="mg-stones__intro">We work with the full spectrum of precious and semi-precious stones. Every stone we use is conflict-free, and where possible, ethically traceable. We'll recommend the right stone for your design, your budget, and your values.</p>
    <div class="ap-materials__grid">
      <div class="ap-material">
        <h3 class="ap-material__name">Diamonds</h3>
        <p class="ap-material__desc">Conflict-free, Kimberley Process compliant. We also offer lab-grown diamonds as an ethical and cost-effective alternative — chemically and visually identical to mined stones.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ap-material">
        <h3 class="ap-material__name">Sapphires</h3>
        <p class="ap-material__desc">From Sri Lanka, Madagascar, and Australia. Available in blue, padparadscha, yellow, pink, and white. One of the most durable coloured stones, ideal for everyday wear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ap-material">
        <h3 class="ap-material__name">Rubies</h3>
        <p class="ap-material__desc">Sourced from ethical suppliers in Mozambique and Madagascar. Rich, deep red to vivid pigeon-blood tones. We provide full provenance on request.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ap-material">
        <h3 class="ap-material__name">Emeralds</h3>
        <p class="ap-material__desc">Colombian and Zambian origins available. A slightly more delicate stone — we'll advise on setting style to protect the stone for long-term wear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ap-material">
        <h3 class="ap-material__name">Semi-precious</h3>
        <p class="ap-material__desc">Aquamarine, tourmaline, morganite, tanzanite, opal, turquoise, and more. Semi-precious stones offer exceptional value and colour range. Ask about availability for your piece.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ap-material">
        <h3 class="ap-material__name">Pearls</h3>
        <p class="ap-material__desc">Akoya, South Sea, and freshwater pearls. We source only from cultivated, responsibly managed pearl farms. Ideal for classic and feminine designs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mg-standard">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <div class="mg-standard__inner">
      <span class="ap-eyebrow">Our standard</span>
      <h2 class="mg-standard__title">Ethical sourcing isn't an add-on.</h2>
      <p>Every metal we use is either recycled or from certified ethical sources. Every stone is conflict-free and Kimberley Process compliant as a minimum. For clients who want to go further, we can source fully traceable, single-origin stones and provide complete documentation.</p>
      <p>We'll never tell you a stone is ethically sourced unless we can prove it. Transparency is part of what you're commissioning when you work with us.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="ap-cta-band">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <h2 class="ap-cta-band__title">Not sure which metal to choose?</h2>
    <p class="ap-cta-band__sub">Tell us how you'll wear it, and we'll recommend the right material during your consultation.</p>
    <a href="/pages/start-your-piece" class="ap-cta-band__btn">Start your commission</a>
  </div>
</section>

